SUVA, Nov. 12 (Xinhua) -- Ratu Wiliame Katonivere was sworn in as the new Fijian president on Friday in a ceremony held at the State House, local media reported. Katonivere took his oath in front of parliament speaker Ratu Epeli Nailatikau, government entourage, diplomats and invited guests. He will become the sixth president since the South Pacific island nation gained independence from Britain in 1970. Katonivere, former president of the ruling party FijiFirst, was appointed as the Fijian president by Parliament last month. Enditem